<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="580" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1124,1692]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,359,1124,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Taxonomic notes.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway, J. D." box="[367,559,1125,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" pagination="1 - 268" refId="ref8779" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2008) The Moths of Borneo: Family Noctuidae, subfamilies Rivulinae, Phytometrinae, Herminiinae, Hypeninae and Hypenodinae. Malayan Nature Journal, 60 (1 - 4), 1 - 268." type="journal article" year="2008">Holloway (2008)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName authority="Wileman, 1915" authorityName="Wileman" authorityYear="1915" box="[723,1117,1124,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Nodaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis box="[723,938,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Nodaria terminalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wileman, A. E." box="[945,1117,1124,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" pagination="34 - 40" refId="ref9178" refString="Wileman, A. E. (1915) New species of Heterocera from Formosa. Entomologist, 48, 34 - 40." type="journal article" year="1915">Wileman, 1915</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[1132,1182,1125,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">type</typeStatus>
locality: Taiwan) with 
<taxonomicName authority="Hampson, 1898" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1898" box="[151,568,1161,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mixomelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis box="[151,384,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Mixomelia decipiens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hampson, G. F." box="[390,568,1161,1187]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" pagination="698 - 724" refId="ref8734" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1898) The moths of India. Supplementary paper to the volumes in &quot; The Fauna of British India &quot;. Part III. Journal of the Bombay Natural History Society, 11, 698 - 724." type="journal article" year="1898">Hampson, 1898</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[582,632,1161,1187]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">type</typeStatus>
locality: Khasi Hills, 
<collectingCountry box="[878,937,1161,1188]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">India</collectingCountry>
) and recorded the geographical range of this species as Himalaya, 
<collectingCountry box="[397,482,1197,1223]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, northern Ryukyus, Borneo, and also gave his view that “the synonymy above may need to be reviewed when variability in the basal ornamentation of the aedeagus vesica can be assessed over a wider range of material.” Though examining abundant material from different collecting localities, we have the opportunity to review the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Nilgiri Hills, Khasi Hills" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[378,599,1305,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Herminia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis box="[378,599,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Herminia decipiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex. Our study shows that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wileman" authorityYear="1915" box="[963,1111,1305,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Nodaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis box="[963,1111,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">H. terminalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Nilgiri Hills, Khasi Hills" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[1296,1436,1305,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Herminia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis box="[1296,1316,1306,1331]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1330,1436,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">decipiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is restricted to 
<collectingCountry box="[360,446,1341,1367]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. The true 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Nilgiri Hills, Khasi Hills" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[554,694,1341,1367]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Herminia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis box="[554,574,1342,1367]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[588,694,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">decipiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in Nilgiri Hills, Khasi Hills, South 
<collectingCountry box="[1237,1307,1341,1367]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">China</collectingCountry>
, Indochina, Malay Peninsula. The populations occurring in other regions represent three new species, i.e. 
<taxonomicName authority="Owada &amp; Wu, 2019" authorityName="Owada &amp; Wu" authorityYear="2019" box="[1217,1337,1377,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Herminia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yuksam" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1217,1337,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">H. yuksam</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1345,1436,1377,1403]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1345,1436,1377,1403]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(East 
<collectingCountry box="[217,287,1413,1439]" name="Nepal" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, Sikkim), 
<taxonomicName authority="Owada &amp; Wu, 2019" authorityName="Owada &amp; Wu" authorityYear="2019" box="[403,517,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Herminia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borneo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[403,517,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">H. borneo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[525,616,1413,1439]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[525,616,1413,1439]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(endemic to Borneo), 
<taxonomicName authority="Owada &amp; Wu, 2019" authorityName="Owada &amp; Wu" authorityYear="2019" box="[871,1063,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Herminia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amamioshima" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[871,1063,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">H. amamioshima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1071,1162,1413,1439]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1071,1162,1413,1439]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(Amami-oshima Island, Shimo-Koshikijima 
<collectingCountry box="[379,447,1449,1475]" name="Iceland" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Island</collectingCountry>
and Kagoshima in South Kyushu).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1124,1692]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1484,1511]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Nilgiri Hills, Khasi Hills" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[379,599,1485,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Herminia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis box="[379,599,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Herminia decipiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex can be separated from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[1116,1223,1486,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Herminia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1116,1223,1486,1511]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Herminia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the less distinct wing fasciae, the more and less dark shade at posterior half part of forewing, the markedly large hairy tibial sheath and minute tarsus of male foreleg (
<bibRefCitation author="Owada, M." box="[611,758,1557,1583]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" refId="ref8901" refString="Owada, M. (1987) A taxonomic study on the subfamily Herminiinae of Japan (Lepidoptera, Noctuidae). National Science Museum, Tokyo, 208 pp." type="book" year="1987">Owada 1987</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 206), and the rather long valval costal process and apical part of valve.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1124,1692]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1628,1655]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Distribution.</emphasis>
The Himalayan region, South 
<collectingCountry box="[698,758,1629,1655]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">India</collectingCountry>
, South 
<collectingCountry box="[842,912,1629,1655]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">China</collectingCountry>
, Indochina, Malay Peninsula, Borneo, 
<collectingCountry box="[1347,1432,1629,1655]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,215,1665,1691]" name="Japan" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Japan</collectingCountry>
(Amami-oshima Is., Shimo-Koshikijima Is. and South Kyushu).
</paragraph>
